            "author_info": {
                "name": "Simran Patel",
                "href": "/profile/Simran-Patel-96"
            },
            "answer_text": "Of course, we do. Though we may not hand-write it but many of us do write something for that someone special. Whether it be our crush, our love, or our boyfriend. We do write down our feelings though they might not be accepted but just for the sake of loving we write our feelings. Sometimes we know that the person that we are writing for might never read it but we still write that heartfelt letter. But, it\u2019s another feeling when that pen hits the paper and off we are describing our feelings for someone. Though not always is the letter written for that someone special. We write it for our friends, parents, family, and many other people. Personally I have written a few love letters. Many of them to my family members on their birthdays. Though none of them have read it but those were filled with memories. And there are many other letters that I have written not all of them were for my family though but all of them are really close to my heart. Many of the letters I have written are close to me and really special but I lost them and haven\u2019t written them again ever since but one day I will write them in a special diary which would only be read by me and others close to me. Lots of love, Simran Patel ",
