                "name": "Sarah Wahid Khan",
                "href": "/profile/Sarah-Wahid-Khan"
            },
            "answer_text": "In the last phase of the night when half of the world has slept breathing stillness into their blood and lost in the dreams of their loved ones, I,an insomniac (still awake) standing in the balcony of my room trying to pull out a curtain on the moon so that the lovers of the midnight can embrace eachother instead. Its 3:30 am and the wind is drifting me back the night when I fell in love with him and for the very first time I wrote to him. I decided to write to him again. (I use to write something daily for my love) I opened my diary and again dissolved him in the ink of each word I framed on the paper   (Entirely a piece of fiction) This is not for the first time I have written a letter to him but its one of the hundredth out of my aggitated nights when I try to forge a single face out of hundreds of faces. Though, I haven\u2019t seen him and don\u2019t have address to post those letters but sometimes I want to cup his face in my palm like the Oyester surrounding a pearl and entangle his hair in between my fingers. I wish to see him someday :) ;) Love ",
